-----------------------------
1 Hudson Debian packages
-----------------------------

Hudson can be installed as a Debian package, which enables:

* Automatic upgrade of Hudson via apt
* /etc/init.d hook up to start Hudson on boot 

To use the repository, first add the key to your system:

	wget -O /tmp/key http://hudson-ci.org/debian/hudson-ci.org.key
	sudo apt-key add /tmp/key

Install dependencies

	sudo apt-get install daemon

Then install Hudson

	wget -O /tmp/hudson.deb http://hudson-ci.org/latest/debian/hudson.deb
	sudo dpkg --install /tmp/hudson.deb

Once the package is installed, apt-get update; apt-get install hudson will update Hudson. See Wiki for more information.


-----------------------------
2 Install Hudson plugins
----------------------------- 

Loginto hudson at localhost:8080 and add the following plugins

* Email-ext plugin
* Git Plugin
* Github plugin
* View Job Filters

-----------------------------
3 Configure Hudson and slave nodes
----------------------------- 
create ssh-key and upload it to github

	ssh-keygen
	
tell github who hudson is

	git config --global user.email florian.weisshardt@ipa.fhg.de
	git config --global user.name ipa320
	
allow hudson user to permanently use sudo rights by adding this line at the end of /etc/sudoers with sudo visudo

hudson ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: ALL

-----------------------------
4 Generate hudson jobs
----------------------------- 

execute create job script

	./create_job.sh GITHUBUSER REPOSITORY ROSRELEASE [EMAIL]
